### Layer 1 & 2 — Frontend Files

#### [NEW] `frontend/Dockerfile`
Multi-stage build: Node 20 builds the Vite app → Nginx serves the dist.

#### [NEW] `frontend/nginx.conf`
Required by the Dockerfile. Routes all traffic to `index.html` for React Router to work (SPA config). Without this, browser refresh on `/admin` or any route will return 404 from Nginx.

---

### Layer 3 — Backend Files

#### [NEW] `backend/Dockerfile`
Python 3.11-slim image. Installs requirements, collects static files, runs Gunicorn.

> [!WARNING]
> The current `requirements.txt` includes `mssql-django` and `pyodbc` which require Microsoft ODBC drivers that are NOT available in standard Linux Docker images. We need to either:
> - Add ODBC driver installation steps to the Dockerfile, OR
> - Switch to PostgreSQL (`psycopg2-binary`) for the Docker environment

#### [NEW] `backend/requirements-docker.txt`
A Docker-specific requirements file that replaces the MSSQL drivers with PostgreSQL (`psycopg2-binary`) since MSSQL requires heavy system-level drivers that inflate image size.

---

### Root Level — Orchestration Files

#### [NEW] `docker-compose.yml` (at project root)
